title: BREAKING: Several feared dead in Paris after two explosions tear through houses
text:
Published 2nd February 2017 
TWITTER 
The death toll is currently unknown after the blast ripped through homes in Noisy-le-Grand in Paris. 
30 firefighters rushed to the scene to battle the aftermath of the double blast. Paris attacks: Suspect Salah Abdeslam shot & arrested Friday, 18th March 2016 The most wanted IS memember Salah Abdeslam was shot and arrested in a counter terrorism raid in Brussels, said to be linked to last year's Paris attacks, in which 130 people died. 1 / 81 Sky News Paris attacks suspect Salah Abdeslam shot and arrested in Brussels 
Captain Guillaume Fresse of the city's fire department said: "The explosion that took place in a house was followed by a fire. 
"According to a provisional report, there are four casualties." 
France has been on high alert after a wave of terror attacks across Europe. 
MORE TO FOLLOW
